#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn5.9"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn5.9:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn5.9:0.2"
msgid "1. Bhikkhunīvagga "
msgstr "1. Nuns "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn5.9:0.3"
msgid "9. Selāsutta "
msgstr "9. With Selā "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn5.9:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn5.9:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho selā bhikkhunī pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā … pe … "
msgstr "Then the nun Selā robed up in the morning … "

msgctxt "sn5.9:1.3"
msgid "aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṃ nisīdi. "
msgstr "and sat at the root of a tree for the day’s meditation. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn5.9:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā selāya bhikkhuniyā bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃsaṃ uppādetukāmo … pe … "
msgstr "Then Māra the Wicked, wanting to make the nun Selā feel fear, terror, and goosebumps … "

msgctxt "sn5.9:1.5"
msgid "selaṃ bhikkhuniṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "addressed her in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn5.9:2.1"
msgid "“Kenidaṃ pakataṃ bimbaṃ, "
msgstr "“Who created this puppet? "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: kvanu → kvannu (bj, pts1-2) | kvaci (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn5.9:2.2"
msgid "kvanu bimbassa kārako; "
msgstr "Where is its maker? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn5.9:2.3"
msgid "Kvanu bimbaṃ samuppannaṃ, "
msgstr "Where has the puppet arisen? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn5.9:2.4"
msgid "kvanu bimbaṃ nirujjhatī”ti. "
msgstr "And where does it cease?” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.295, sc3
msgctxt "sn5.9:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho selāya bhikkhuniyā etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then the nun Selā thought, "

msgctxt "sn5.9:3.2"
msgid "“ko nu khvāyaṃ manusso vā amanusso vā gāthaṃ bhāsatī”ti? "
msgstr "“Who’s speaking this verse, a human or a non-human?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn5.9:3.3"
msgid "Atha kho selāya bhikkhuniyā etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then she thought, "

msgctxt "sn5.9:3.4"
msgid "“māro kho ayaṃ pāpimā mama bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃsaṃ uppādetukāmo samādhimhā cāvetukāmo gāthaṃ bhāsatī”ti. "
msgstr "“This is Māra the Wicked, wanting to make me feel fear, terror, and goosebumps, wanting to make me fall away from immersion!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn5.9:3.5"
msgid "Atha kho selā bhikkhunī “māro ayaṃ pāpimā” iti viditvā māraṃ pāpimantaṃ gāthāhi paccabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then Selā, knowing that this was Māra the Wicked, replied to him in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
#. VAR: Nayidaṃ attakataṃ → nayidaṃ pakataṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn5.9:4.1"
msgid "“Nayidaṃ attakataṃ bimbaṃ, "
msgstr "“This puppet isn’t self-made, "

# NOTE: Note the confused readings here. neither of the two Chinese parallels at SA2 219 or SA 1203 contain any parallel to agha.
#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: nayidaṃ parakataṃ → nayidaṃ pakataṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn5.9:4.2"
msgid "nayidaṃ parakataṃ aghaṃ; "
msgstr "nor is this misery made by another. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn5.9:4.3"
msgid "Hetuṃ paṭicca sambhūtaṃ, "
msgstr "It comes to be because of a cause, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn5.9:4.4"
msgid "hetubhaṅgā nirujjhati. "
msgstr "and ceases when the cause breaks up. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn5.9:5.1"
msgid "Yathā aññataraṃ bījaṃ, "
msgstr "It’s like a seed that’s sown "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn5.9:5.2"
msgid "khette vuttaṃ virūhati; "
msgstr "in a field; it grows "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn5.9:5.3"
msgid "Pathavīrasañcāgamma, "
msgstr "relying on both the soil’s nutrients "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn5.9:5.4"
msgid "sinehañca tadūbhayaṃ. "
msgstr "as well as moisture. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn5.9:6.1"
msgid "Evaṃ khandhā ca dhātuyo, "
msgstr "In the same way the aggregates and elements "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn5.9:6.2"
msgid "cha ca āyatanā ime; "
msgstr "and these six sense fields "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn5.9:6.3"
msgid "Hetuṃ paṭicca sambhūtā, "
msgstr "come to be because of a cause, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn5.9:6.4"
msgid "hetubhaṅgā nirujjhare”ti. "
msgstr "and cease when the cause breaks up.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn5.9:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā “jānāti maṃ selā bhikkhunī”ti dukkhī dummano tatthevantaradhāyīti. "
msgstr "Then Māra the Wicked, thinking, “The nun Selā knows me!” miserable and sad, vanished right there."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
